main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a round, silver object in Seattle, Washington in June 1947.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 3,000 feet,The object was observed to be moving at a slow speed,The report lacks substantial data and is concluded as insufficient for evaluation,The shape of the object was described as round and silver,No photographs or physical evidence were available in the report
sighted object: round, silver object in the sky
